{
  "stem": "7506.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And when we arrived there, a uniformed Dutch person-- in uniform same as the British uniform, khaki uniform-- asked us questions about our name, our father's name, mother's name, the last address we were at in Holland, which camp we came from.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And that form, that card, I've kept all my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And a few years ago, I donated the original to the Washington Holocaust Museum.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While I was in the camp-- after the liberation-- every day before we were taken out of the camp to go to the hospital, the Germans and Hungarians-- there were Hungarian soldiers there who had been deprived of their weapons by the Allies, as indeed were the Germans deprived of their weapons.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were all commanded to move the bodies-- to take the bodies, pick them up, throw them into trucks and into wagons to be transported to the mass graves.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while I was still in the camp, I used to see them just with bulldozers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Just after the mass grave was dug there, the bulldozers would just bulldoze all the people into the graves.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And where the bulldozers couldn't come because of the narrowness between the barracks where the people-- the dead bodies, the corpses-- were laying, the little truck would come, or the trolley would come.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Germans, under guard of British soldiers with weapons-- either Tommy guns or rifles-- the Germans would have to load the corpses onto those vehicles for them to be taken to the mass grave.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This happened virtually day and night in the camp after liberation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A great amount of joy amongst us children and the adults that were still able to walk.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The ones that could not walk, sitting down, couldn't get up, laying in the dirt, couldn't move, too sick.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
